# Styling Patterns

## Overview

Always use Tailwind CSS for styling and shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui`. Use the `cn()` utility for conditional class merging.

## Import Statements

```typescript
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Card } from "@/components/ui/card";
// Import other shadcn/ui components as needed
```

## Tailwind CSS

### Basic Usage

Always use Tailwind utility classes for styling:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Using Tailwind classes
export function Component() {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center justify-center min-h-screen bg-background">
      <h1 className="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Welcome</h1>
    </div>
  );
}
```

```typescript
// ❌ INCORRECT: Using inline styles or CSS modules
export function Component() {
  return (
    <div style={{ display: "flex", alignItems: "center" }}>
      <h1 className={styles.title}>Welcome</h1>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Conditional Classes

Use `cn()` utility for conditional and merged classes:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Using cn() for conditional classes
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

export function Button({ variant, disabled }: Props) {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        "px-4 py-2 rounded-md",
        variant === "primary" && "bg-blue-500 text-white",
        variant === "secondary" && "bg-gray-500 text-white",
        disabled && "opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed"
      )}
    >
      Click me
    </button>
  );
}
```

```typescript
// ❌ INCORRECT: Manual class string concatenation
export function Button({ variant, disabled }: Props) {
  let className = "px-4 py-2 rounded-md";
  if (variant === "primary") className += " bg-blue-500 text-white";
  if (disabled) className += " opacity-50";
  return <button className={className}>Click me</button>;
}
```

## shadcn/ui Components

### Component Usage

Always import and use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui`:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Using shadcn/ui components
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent } from "@/components/ui/card";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";

export function Component() {
  return (
    <Card>
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle>Title</CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <Input placeholder="Enter text" />
        <Button>Submit</Button>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  );
}
```

### Component Variants

Use component variants provided by shadcn/ui:

```typescript
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

export function Component() {
  return (
    <div>
      <Button variant="default">Default</Button>
      <Button variant="destructive">Delete</Button>
      <Button variant="outline">Outline</Button>
      <Button variant="secondary">Secondary</Button>
      <Button variant="ghost">Ghost</Button>
      <Button variant="link">Link</Button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Customizing Components

Extend shadcn/ui components with Tailwind classes:

```typescript
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

export function CustomButton({ className, ...props }: ButtonProps) {
  return <Button className={cn("custom-classes-here", className)} {...props} />;
}
```

## Best Practices

### DO

- ✅ Always use Tailwind utility classes
- ✅ Always use `cn()` for conditional and merged classes
- ✅ Always import components from `@/components/ui`
- ✅ Use shadcn/ui component variants when available
- ✅ Follow shadcn/ui component API patterns
- ✅ Use semantic HTML with Tailwind classes
- ✅ Leverage Tailwind's responsive utilities

### DON'T

- ❌ Don't use inline styles
- ❌ Don't use CSS modules or styled-components
- ❌ Don't create custom components that duplicate shadcn/ui functionality
- ❌ Don't modify shadcn/ui component files directly
- ❌ Don't use manual string concatenation for classes

